.DS_Store
node_modules
# Cover every local env file, not just the exact name: setup-production.sh writes generated
# EENGINE_SECRET/REDIS_PASSWORD/SMTP_PASSWORD into .env and then backs it up as
# .env.backup.<timestamp>, which a bare `.env` rule does not match.
.env*
# ...except the two committed templates. They carry only self-labelled dev defaults and
# CHANGE_ME placeholders, never real credentials, and are already tracked.
!.env.development
!.env.production
dist/
yarn.lock
swagger.json
version-info.json
ee-dist/
config/development*
.vscode
.okta.env
keylog.txt
.claude
issue*
patch*
manual-test/
playwright-report/
test-results/
blob-report/
playwright/.cache/
*-plan.md

# Profiling and crash artifacts - never commit these, they capture process memory
*.heapsnapshot
*.cpuprofile
*.heapprofile
core.*

# Local logs
*.log
